3EThe%20PM%202.5%20pollutant%20is%20often%20termed%20as%20a%20killer%20and%20is%20a%20major%20component%20of%20air%20pollution%20in%20urban%20areas.%20The%20study%20suggests%20that%20short-term%20exposure%20to%20PM%202.5%20increases%20the%20risk%20of%20insulin%20resistance%20by%20triggering%20the%20autonomic%20nervous%20system%2C%20which%20is%20a%20pathway%20toward%20cardiovascular%20diseases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20found%20that%20a%20monthly%20exposure%20to%20PM%202.5%20pollutants%20led%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20blood%20sugar%20levels%20and%20a%20prolonged%20exposure%20(almost%20a%20year)%20led%20to%20a%2020%25%20increase%20in%20risk%20of%20type%202%20diabetes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20link%20between%20air%20pollution%20and%20diabetes%20is%20higher%20in%20men%20groups%20from%20lower%20socioeconomic%20groups%20and%20those%20with%20comorbidities.%20Evidence%20suggests%20that%20PM2.5%20is%20associated%20with%20chronic%20kidney%20disease%20in%20populations%20both%20with%20and%20without%20diabetes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAround%20537%20million%20suffer%20from%20type%202%20diabetes%20and%20half%20of%20them%20are%20unaware%20that%20they%20are%20diabetic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20in%20India%2C%20an%20estimated%2077%20million%20people%20above%20the%20age%20of%2018%20years%20are%20suffering%20from%20diabetes%20(type%202)%20and%20nearly%2025%20million%20are%20prediabetics%20(at%20a%20higher%20risk%20of%20developing%20diabetes%20in%20the%20future)%2C%20according%20to%20WHO.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPolluted%20Air%20In%20Indian%20Cities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdelhi-worlds-most-polluted-capital-city-again-report-5265746%5C%22%3EBihar's%20Begusarai%20emerged%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20the%20world's%20most%20polluted%20metropolitan%20area%20while%20Delhi%20was%20identified%20as%20the%20capital%20city%20with%20the%20poorest%20air%20quality%2C%20according%20to%20the%20World%20Air%20Quality%20Report.%20The%20national%20capital%20has%20ranked%20the%20most%20polluted%20capital%20city%20in%20the%20world%20four%20times%20since%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20an%20average%20annual%20PM2.5%20concentration%20of%2054.4%20micrograms%20per%20cubic%20metre%2C%20India%20had%20the%20third%20worst%20air%20quality%20out%20of%20134%20countries%20in%202023%20after%20Bangladesh%20(79.9%20micrograms%20per%20cubic%20metre)%20and%20Pakistan%20(73.7%20micrograms%20per%20cubic%20metre)%2C%20according%20to%20the%20World%20Air%20Quality%20Report%202023%20by%20Swiss%20organisation%20IQAir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20India%20was%20ranked%20as%20the%20eighth%20most%20polluted%20country%20with%20an%20average%20PM2.5%20concentration%20of%2053.3%20micrograms%20per%20cubic%20metre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20estimated%20that%201.36%20billion%20people%20in%20India%20experience%20PM2.5%20concentrations%20exceeding%20the%20World%20Health%20Organisation%20(WHO)%20recommended%20annual%20guideline%20level%20of%205%20micrograms%20per%20cubic%20metre%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E-%20With%20inputs%20from%20PTI%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714369080000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2F259tq5g8_delhi-air-pollution-pti_625x300_03_November_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F20-type-2-diabetes-cases-linked-to-air-pollution-says-lancet-study-5546981%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Prolonged%20exposure%20to%20polluted%20air%20with%20PM%202.5%20particulate%20matter%2C%20which%20is%2030%20times%20thinner%20than%20a%20strand%20of%20hair%2C%20can%20increase%20the%20risk%20of%20type%202%20diabetes%2C%20a%20new%20study%20suggests.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F20-type-2-diabetes-cases-linked-to-air-pollution-says-lancet-study-5546981%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%