her%20late%20husband%2C%20Leonard%20Gordon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDue%20to%20her%20age%2C%20Moreno%20often%20needs%20to%20rely%20on%20her%20daughter%20for%20assistance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20constantly%20calling%20upon%20her%20to%20do%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20Moreno%20told%20People.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20a%20problem%20with%20remembering%20names%2C%20names%20of%20things%2C%20and%20names%20of%20people.%20It's%20so%20much%20a%20part%20of%20being%2092%20right%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAside%20from%20getting%20help%20with%20simple%20tasks%2C%20Moreno%20says%20she%20depends%20on%20Gordon%20for%20advice%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20times%20when%20I%20need%20her%20wisdom%2C%20and%20they%20are%20more%20often%20than%20you%20might%20think%2C%20particularly%20at%20this%20age.%20Ninety-two%20is%20not%20easy%20in%20many%20ways%2C%20and%20it's%20something%20that's%20difficult%20to%20understand%2C%26quot%3B%20Moreno%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20death%20isn't%20something%20that%20she%20discusses%20with%20her%20daughter%2C%20the%20actor%20says%20she%20knows%20she%20won't%20live%20forever%2C%20and%20that's%20why%20they%20try%20to%20spend%20as%20much%20time%20together%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20as%20you%2C%20the%20parent%2C%20gets%20older%2C%20I%20believe%20that%20the%20child%20has%20to%20be%20thinking%20about%2C%20'Well%2C%20at%20some%20point%20this%20will%20end%2C'%26quot%3B%20Moreno%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20we're%20both%20pretty%20brave%20about%20it.%20Well%2C%20we're%20really%20honest%20%E2%80%94%20very%2C%20very%20honest%20with%20each%20other.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20now%2C%20they%20still%20do%20a%20lot%20of%20things%20together%2C%20like%20traveling%20and%20shopping.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20constantly%20have%20people%20picking%20up%20on%20our%20closeness%20and%20commenting%2C%20'I%20wish%20I%20felt%20that%20way%20about%20my%20mom!'%26quot%3B%20Gordon%20told%20People%20in%20the%20same%20in