%26quot%3Bdeceptive%20claims%20and%20follow%20Made%20in%20USA%20requirements%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20a%20press%20release%20shared%20by%20the%20FTC.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ledmonds%40businessinsider.com%20(Lauren%20Edmonds)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A40%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwilliams-sonoma-pay-3-million-false-made-in-usa-claims-2024-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20a%20federal%20prison%20consultant.%20Here's%20how%20I%20went%20from%20being%20in%20prison%20to%20helping%20clients%20get%20ready%20to%20go%20behind%20bars.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sam%20Mangel.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F662dc95f10dfcda40964387a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221125%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESam%20Mangel.%3Cp%3EKenneth%20A%20Appelbaum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESam%20Mangel%2C%20a%20former%20convict%2C%20now%20works%20as%20a%20federal%20prison%20consultant.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20uses%20his%20personal%20experience%20to%20help%20defendants%20navigate%20the%20system%20and%20reduce%20their%20sentences.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAfter%20spending%20time%20in%20custody%2C%20Mangel%20learned%20that%20knowledge%20is%20power%20in%20prison.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsam-mangel.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESam%20Mangel%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20a%20federal%20prison%20consultant%20with%20his%20own%20firm.%20Mangel%20went%20into%20the%20field%20after%20pleading%20guilty%20to%20wire%20fraud%20in%20an%20insurance%20fraud%20scheme%20and%20being%20sentenced%20to%20time%20in%20prison.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20I%20had%20been%20retired%20from%20my%20work%20in%20insurance%20for%20four%20years.%20I%20got%20a%20knock%20on%20the%20door%20of%20my%20house%20in%20Florida%20at%207%20o'clock%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20and%20it%20was%2017%20men%20and%20women%20wearing%20blue%20FBI%20windbreakers%20and%20holding%20guns.%20I%20thought%20for%20sure%20they%20were%20there%20asking%20directions%20for%20a%20neighbor%20or%20something.%20Once%20I%20identified%20myself%2C%20they%20handcuffed%20me%20and%20put%20me%20in%20the%20back%20of%20the%20car.%20I%20had%20no%20idea%20what%20was%20happening.%20I%20hadn't%20been%20in%20any%20business%20during%20that%20time%20period.%20An%20FBI%20agent%20told%20me%20in%20the%20car%20that%20I%20was%20being%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fusao-edpa%2Fpr%2Fflorida-man-charged-insurance-fraud-violations%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echarged%20out%20of%20Philadelphia%20with%20wire%20fraud%20and%20insurance%20fraud%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20retained%20an%20attorney%20and%20spent%20half%20a%20million%20dollars%20for%20a%20big%20firm.%20I%20handed%20over%20my%20check%2C%20and%20I%20remember%20him%20giving%20me%20seven%20phone%20numbers%20he%20could%20be%20reached%20at%2024%2F7.%20I%20called%20him%20on%20Monday%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20hear%20back%20from%20him%20until%20Thursday.%20That's%20when%20I%20realized%20that%20to%20a%20criminal%20defense%20attorney%2C%20you're%20just%20a%20number.%20It's%20a%20very%20transactional%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESix%20months%20later%2C%20my%20attorney%20told%20me%20I%20had%20to%20take%20a%20plea%2C%20but%20he%20said%20he%20could%20negotiate%20for%20one%20year%20non-custodial.%20I%20went%20in%20for%20the%20pre-sentencing%20interview%2C%20and%20it%20was%20contentious.%20I%20didn't%20understand%20the%20nuances%20of%20it.%20When%20it%20came%20time%20for%20sentencing%2C%20the%20judge%20looked%20down%20at%20me%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BMr.%20Mangel%2C%20you%20clearly%20have%20no%20remorse.%26quot%3B%20He%20deviated%20upward%20from%20sentencing%20recommendations%2C%20gave%20me%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdigitalcommons.law.villanova.edu%2Fcgi%2Fviewcontent.cgi%3Farticle%3D1843%26context%3Dthirdcircuit_2019%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E60%20months%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20remanded%20me%20to%20custody.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20thing%20that%20went%20through%20my%20mind%20was%20that%20on%20a%2060-month%20sentence%20under%20the%20federal%20statute%20at%20the%20time%2C%20I%20have%20to%20serve%2085%25%20of%20that.%20So%2C%20I%20was%20going%20to%20be%20away%20from%20my%20family%20for%20four%20years%20and%20a%20few%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20I%20was%20in%20custody%2C%20I%20made%20a%20sarcastic%20joke%20about%20how%20I%20drink%20like%20a%20fish.%20Because%20I%20made%20that%20statement%20to%20a%20staffer%2C%20out%20of%20pure%20dumb%20luck%2C%20I%20got%20into%20RDAP%2C%20which%20is%20the%209-month%20drug%20and%20alcohol%20program.%20That%20immediately%20took%2012%20months%20off%20my%20sentence.%20That's%20how%20I%20learned%20that%20in%20prison%2C%20knowledge%20is%20king.%20Knowledge%20is%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20a%20year%20later%2C%20I%20got%20my%20initial%20release%2C%20and%20I%20ended%20up%20with%2012%20months%20in%20a%20halfway%20house%20and%20home%20confinement.%20Then%20COVID%20came%2C%20and%20with%20the%20CARES%20Act%2C%20Congress%20was%20looking%20to%20release%20eligible%20inmates.%20Previously%2C%20I%20had%20helped%20out%20a%20warden%20with%20some%20questions%20about%20his%20bicycle%2C%20and%20he%20promised%20me%20a%20favor.%20I%20called%20it%20in%2C%20and%20he%20made%20me%20the%20test%20case%20for%20the%20CARES%20Act.%20He%20told%20me%20I%20was%20the%20first%20person%20in%20the%20southeast%20region%20to%20be%20released%20under%20the%20CARES%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20out%20in%20March%20of%202020%20and%20then%20got%20off%20supervised%20release%20early.%20I%20convinced%20a%20judge%20in%20Florida%20that%20I%20was%20non-risk%20and%20compliant%2C%20so%20instead%20of%20serving%2036%20months%20of%20supervised%20release%2C%20it%20was%20dropped%20down%20to%20about%2023%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20into%20this%20business%20because%20when%20I%20was%20in%20custody%2C%20I%20met%20other%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-white-house-advisor-navarro-transitions-to-miami-prison-life-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhite-collar%20offenders%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20had%20much%20lower%20sentences%20for%20worse%20charges%20than%20mine.%20They%20worked%20with%20consultants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20can%20do%20that.%20I%20understand%20the%20system%20and%20the%20mentality%20of%20people%20dealing%20with%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20being%20available%20to%20a%20defendant%20and%20their%20family%20is%20the%20most%20important%20thing%20and%20part%20of%20being%20a%20consultant.%20Yes%2C%20I%20can%20help%20somebody%20get%20designated%20to%20the%20right%20place%20or%20into%20the%20right%20programs.%20Ultimately%2C%20especially%20before%20surrender%2C%20it's%20about%20bringing%20down%20the%20temperature.%20There's%20nothing%20scarier%20than%20dealing%20with%20the%20800-pound%20gorilla%20that%20is%20the%20government%2C%20an%20unresponsive%20attorney%2C%20and%20the%20unknown.%20Prison%20is%20a%20black%20hole%2C%20and%20attorneys%20don't%20know%20about%20prison%20because%20it's%20not%20their%20job%20to%20know%20about%20it.%20They've%20never%20been%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20ask%20myself%20how%20can%20I%20help%20clients%20in%20a%20non-legal%20manner%20get%20the%20best%20outcome%20at%20sentencing%3F%20In%20my%20case%2C%20I%20was%20my%20own%20worst%20enemy%20because%20I%20had%20no%20humility.%20How%20do%20I%20help%20people%20prepare%20for%20that%20pre-sentence%20interview%3F%20How%20do%20we%20use%20the%20number%20of%20months%20the%20judge%20reads%20out%20as%20a%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-bankman-fried-serve-less-time-controls-impulses-sentencing-prison-2024-3%5C%22