0https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FManganga-river-before_11zon-1713963784-150x84.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-348185%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221314%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20state%20of%20the%20river%20before%20its%20rejuvenation.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHaving%20read%20the%20book%20I%20realised%20that%20the%20task%20of%20revitalising%20the%20river%20could%20not%20be%20done%20just%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3Eshramdan%20%3C%2Fem%3E(service)%20of%20a%20handful%20of%20villagers.%20We%20needed%20earth%20movers%20to%20do%20it%2C%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Shriharsha%20Phene%2C%20the%20secretary%20of%20the%20Mumbai-based%20charitable%20foundation%2C%20Shree%20Brihad%20Bhartiya%20Samaj.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%20it%20took%20to%20clean%20the%20river%2C%20the%20foundation%20donated%20Rs%201.53%20crores.%20Others%2C%20too%2C%20joined%20in%20with%20their%20cheques%20including%20the%20Sangli-based%20Sadguru%20Sri%20Sri%20Sakhar%20Karkhana%20trust%2C%20Naam%20Foundation%2C%20along%20with%20a%20local%20MLA%2C%20and%20a%20Pune-based%20industrialist%20named%20Sudamrao%20Bhore%2C%20among%20several%20others.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20was%20born%20and%20raised%20in%20Sangola%E2%80%99s%20Wasudh%20village%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20the%2054-year-old%20Bhore.%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20how%20could%20I%20not%20contribute%20to%20the%20task%20undertaken%20by%20Ghongade%20sir%20to%20revive%20the%20river%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20excavation%20was%20generally%20undertaken%20during%20the%20summer%20months%20and%20it%20took%20six%20years%20to%20clean%20the%2075-km%20long%20stretch%20of%20the%20river%20and%20a%20total%20of%2020%20lakh%20cubic%20metres%20of%20silt%20was%20removed%20from%20the%20river%20bed.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAccording%20to%20the%20irrigation%20department%20officials%2C%20it%20would%20have%20cost%20Rs%209%20crore%2C%20but%20we%20did%20this%20work%20for%20less%20than%20Rs%203%20crores%2C%20thanks%20to%20the%20monetary%20contribution%20from%20the%20community%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Ghongade%2C%20who%20braved%20the%20summer%20heat%20to%20oversee%20the%20work%2C%20year%20after%20year%2C%20despite%20his%20advanced%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%202407px)%20100vw%2C%202407px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FThe-flowing-Manganga-river-after-rejuvenation-_11zon-1713963903.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%222407%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Manganga%20river%20now%2C%20after%20being%20restored%20to%20its%20former%20glory.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FThe-flowing-Manganga-river-after-rejuvenation-_11zon-1713963903.jpg%202407w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FThe-flowing-Manganga-river-after-rejuvenation-_11zon-1713963903-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FThe-flowing-Manganga-river-after-rejuvenation-_11zon-1713963903-500x281.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FThe-flowing-Manganga-river-after-rejuvenation-_11zon-1713963903-768x432.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FThe-flowing-Manganga-river-after-rejuvenation-_11zon-1713963903-1536x863.jpg%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FThe-flowing-Manganga-river-after-rejuvenation-_11zon-1713963903-2048x1151.jpg%202048w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FThe-flowing-Manganga-river-after-rejuvenation-_11zon-1713963903-150x84.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-348188%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221353%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20Manganga%20river%20now%2C%20after%20being%20restored%20to%20its%20former%20glory.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EProsperity%20greeted%20the%20region%20as%20the%20results%20bore%20fruit%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20downpour%20in%20August%202021%2C%20the%20weirs%20started%20overflowing.%20Hundreds%20of%20people%20lined%20up%20on%20the%20river%20banks%2C%20shouting%20with%20joy!%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20a%20sight%20we%20had%20not%20witnessed%20in%20so%20long.%20We%20were%20only%20hoping%20that%20we%20would%20be%20able%20to%20start%20farming%2C%E2%80%9D%20recalls%20Vithal%20Chavan%20(38)%2C%20a%20farmer%20growing%20wheat%20and%20corn%20on%20his%20two-acre%20plot.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERevitalising%20the%20river%20led%20to%20the%20extraction%20of%2020%20lakh%20cubic%20metres%20of%20silt%2C%20thus%20bringing%20back%20322%20acres%20of%20fallow%20land%20under%20cultivation.%20The%20delighted%20farmers%20carried%20the%20silt%20back%20to%20their%20farm%20plots.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavnath%20Dighe%20(43)%2C%20of%20Wadegaon%2C%20is%20among%20the%20192%20farmers%20who%20benefitted%20from%20the%20silt%20excavated%20from%20the%20river.%20%E2%80%9CI%20may%20have%20taken%20more%20than%20600%20tractor%20loads%20of%20silt%20and%20deposited%20it%20on%20my%20three-acre%20plot%20where%20I%20grow%20sugarcane%20using%20drip%20irrigation%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Dighe.%20In%20total%2C%20he%20owns%20eight%20acres%20of%20land%20and%20grows%20finger%20millet%2C%20corn%2C%20as%20well%20as%20raising%20a%20pomegranate%20orchard.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20silt%2C%20rich%20in%20nutrients%2C%20has%20yielded%20a%20better%20harvest.%20Bablu%20Ghongade%20(48)%2C%20a%20sugarcane%20farmer%2C%20informs%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20used%20to%20get%20a%20yield%20of%2035%20tonnes%20per%20acre%20but%20now%20it%E2%80%99s%20around%2050%20tonnes.%20It%E2%80%99s%20all%20due%20to%20the%20silt%20from%20the%20river.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%